Basic Details of the Team and
Problem Statement
Ministry/Organization Name/Student Innovation:
Ministry of Jal Shakti
PS Code: SIH1294
Problem Statement Title: Estimation of inflow to a reservoir from the
rainfall considering soil moisture in its catchment and releases from
upstream reservoirs and automatically opening of reservoir gates
for moderately releasing the water to avoid the flooding in a basin.

Idea/Approach Details
Description of Idea
A large number of sensor modules will be deployed across river basin,
collecting data regarding rainfall, soil moisture, humidity, temperature
These sensor modules will upload the data to an IoT cloud in real-time.
Further data from dams regarding water levels, water releases as well
as water flow in various tributaries is uploaded to the IoT cloud.
Past and present data regarding ecological, geographical factors, water
needs, human settlements, climate data, etc is also fed into the system.
The cloud also gathers data from Weather forecasters, Meteorological
dept, weather satellites, Jal Shakti ministry, and other stakeholders.
The AI system trained with Machine learning, goes through the data
and comes up with possible actions, and then runs predictive
simulations and analyses and chooses the best actions with best
possible outcomes.
Multiple AI systems operate parallelly and then cross verify each
others decisions to ensure safety, and upload final decision to Cloud
The Dam refers to the instructions posted by the AI system on the
cloud, and releases the required water and sends back confirmation.
The AI system again compares the real-world outcomes with its
predictions and uses the data to improve its algorithms through
Machine learning, thus acting as a continuously improving system.
2
Idea/Approach Details
Use Case scenario:
To be used for effective management of a network
of Dams/reservoirs spread across a River basin.
As byproduct, data and insights can also be used to
improve agriculture, economy, water management,
protecting climate, ecological conservation, research, etc
3
Show Stoppers: Advantages in our approach
Takes real-time data from a large number of
sensors: It is thus able to identify rainfall/flood, dam
water level changes at precise locations and react to
it effectively based on the scale of the situation.
AI&ML, Data Science: Our system is able to analyze
the real time data being generated and take required
actions autonomously for the optimal results for
situations using its deep insights of the situation.
Uses Open-Source Arduino + NodeMCU tech:
No intellectual property issues, easily available
hardware, large established ecosystem for hardware.
Scalability : Our system can be easily scaled from
small local streams to networks of huge river basins.
Modularity: All parts to our system can be easily
removed, added to and replaced based on availability
Adaptability and Continuously Evolving: Our
system learns continuously from data from past
situations and actions, user feedbacks, etc to evolve
its algorithms and improve future responses.
Low maintenance + Human intervention required
System is fully autonomous and even the sensor
modules can receive software updates over-the-air
without manual intervention throughout the process
Technologies / Tools being used:
Arduino microcontrollers
NodeMCU+ESP32 WiFi/BLE enabled microcontrollers
Arduino Cloud platforms for IoT
EdgeImpulse ML tools to train AI algorithms
Web API for data transfer and extraction
Development and Testing Status:
Hardware prototypes of Sensor modules mostly complete & being
worked on to optimize data accuracy and transfer to IoT cloud.
AI model being trained on simulated data using Machine Learning
Were working on our own cloud platform to replace 3rd party
Arduino cloud service with our own custom purpose-built IoT cloud
